description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you a hard working and enthusiastic individual looking to start a career in hospital pharmacy. If so, this may be the job for you!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;An exciting vacancy has arisen for a full time post to support the Procurement and distribution team in the sourcing and supply of medicines for Buckinghamshire Healthcare NHS Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder must be self-motivated and confident and an excellent communicator. Excellent IT skills will be required to ensure all processes are carried out accurately and efficiently&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Duties will include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in creating purchase orders for medicines and non-medicinal products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Actively support and participate in stock management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Chase outstanding orders with suppliers investigating MCS issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To assist with Drug Alerts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in co-ordinating the Distribution service including the use of the distribution Robots&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Receive and book in stock from suppliers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide Ward Top-up Services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supervising Junior members of staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support dispensary when needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participating in the weekend/bank holiday and late night rota’s&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be required to complete the NVQ level 2 in pharmacy services if this qualification is not already achieved.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our trust has three sites, Stoke Mandeville ,Wycombe and Amersham all providing specialist and acute care.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This is a varied and interesting job role with opportunities for further development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Greg Edwards, Technician Team Manager Procurement &amp; Distribution greg.edwards@nhs.net 01296315280&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;or&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Clem Peters, Technician Team Leader Procurement &amp; Distribution Clem.Peters@nhs.net 01296315280&lt;/p&gt;
